<li id="cite_note-gould-7">^ <a href="#cite_ref-gould_7-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-gould_7-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFGould.2C_Rupert_T.1923"><a href="/wiki/Rupert_Gould" title="Rupert Gould">Gould, Rupert T.</a> (1923). <i>The Marine Chronometer. Its History and Development</i>. London: J. D. Potter. pp.&#160;56. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0907462057" class="internal">ISBN 0-907462-05-7</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Marine+Chronometer.+Its+History+and+Development&amp;rft.aulast=Gould%2C+Rupert+T.&amp;rft.au=Gould%2C+Rupert+T.&amp;rft.date=1923&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B56&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=J.+D.+Potter&amp;rft.isbn=0-907462-05-7&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:John_Harrison"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFVarzeliotis1998">Varzeliotis, A.N. Thomas (1998). <i>Time Under Sail: The Very Human Story of the Marine Chronometer</i>. Alcyone Books. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0921081103" class="internal">ISBN 0-921081-10-3</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Time+Under+Sail%3A+The+Very+Human+Story+of+the+Marine+Chronometer&amp;rft.aulast=Varzeliotis&amp;rft.aufirst=A.N.+Thomas&amp;rft.au=Varzeliotis%2C+A.N.+Thomas&amp;rft.date=1998&amp;rft.pub=Alcyone+Books&amp;rft.isbn=0-921081-10-3&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:John_Harrison"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> Captain James Cook, Richard Hough, Holder and Stroughton 1994.pp 192-193 <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0340585986" class="internal">ISBN 0-340-58598-6</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-landes-10">^ <a href="#cite_ref-landes_10-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-landes_10-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFLandes1983">Landes, David S. (1983). <i>Revolution in Time</i>. Cambridge, MA: Belknap Press of Harvard University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0674768000" class="internal">ISBN 0-674-76800-0</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Revolution+in+Time&amp;rft.aulast=Landes&amp;rft.aufirst=David+S.&amp;rft.au=Landes%2C+David+S.&amp;rft.date=1983&amp;rft.place=Cambridge%2C+MA&amp;rft.pub=Belknap+Press+of+Harvard+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-674-76800-0&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:John_Harrison"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFMercer1972">Mercer, Vaudrey (1972). <i>John Arnold &amp; Son, Chronometer Makers, 1762-1843</i>. The Antiquarian Horological Society.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=John+Arnold+%26+Son%2C+Chronometer+Makers%2C+1762-1843&amp;rft.aulast=Mercer&amp;rft.aufirst=Vaudrey&amp;rft.au=Mercer%2C+Vaudrey&amp;rft.date=1972&amp;rft.pub=The+Antiquarian+Horological+Society&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:John_Harrison"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-king-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-king_12-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFKing2000">King, Dean (2000). <i>A Sea of Words</i>. New York: Henry Holt and Co.. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780805066159" class="internal">ISBN 978-0805066159</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+Sea+of+Words&amp;rft.aulast=King&amp;rft.aufirst=Dean&amp;rft.au=King%2C+Dean&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Henry+Holt+and+Co.&amp;rft.isbn=978-0805066159&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:John_Harrison"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>This book has a table showing that at the peak just prior to the <a href="/wiki/War_of_1812" title="War of 1812">War of 1812</a>, Britain's <a href="/wiki/Royal_Navy" title="Royal Navy">Royal Navy</a> had almost 1000 ships. By 1840, this number had reduced to only 200. Even though the navy only officially equipped their vessels with chronometers after 1825, this shows that the number of chronometers required by the navy was shrinking in the early 19<sup>th</sup> century.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Mortzen-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Mortzen_13-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFMortzen1993">Mortzen, Willem F.J. (1993). <i>The Astronomical Clocks of Andeas Hohnu: A Checklist</i>. Making Instruments Count, Variorum. pp.&#160;459. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0860783944" class="internal">ISBN 0-86078-394-4</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Astronomical+Clocks+of+Andeas+Hohnu%3A+A+Checklist&amp;rft.aulast=Mortzen&amp;rft.aufirst=Willem+F.J.&amp;rft.au=Mortzen%2C+Willem+F.J.&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B459&amp;rft.pub=Making+Instruments+Count%2C+Variorum&amp;rft.isbn=0-86078-394-4&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:John_Harrison"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>Mortzen identifies a recession starting around 1857 that depressed shipping and the need for chronometers.</li>
<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFBetts2006">Betts, Jonathan (2006). <i>Time restored: The Harrison Timekeepers and R.T. Gould, the man who knew (almost) everything</i>. Oxford: Oxford University Press. pp.&#160;464. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780198568025" class="internal">ISBN 978-0-19-856802-5</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Time+restored%3A+The+Harrison+Timekeepers+and+R.T.+Gould%2C+the+man+who+knew+%28almost%29+everything&amp;rft.aulast=Betts&amp;rft.aufirst=Jonathan&amp;rft.au=Betts%2C+Jonathan&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B464&amp;rft.place=Oxford&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-19-856802-5&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:John_Harrison"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ol>
